{
  "stem": "26111.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "This was perfect.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "This was absolutely perfect for him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And so the propaganda people-- Goebbels, et cetera, and his henchmen-- they dreamed up a, a plot to, to assassinate this great patriot, vom Rath.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Vom Rath was the name of the consular that was shot dead.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And the German people was to arise in spontaneous punishment and, and rage against the, the Jewish oppressor and the-- in our midst.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And that's what they did-- Kristallnacht, of course, because they smashed every window in sight-- of any Jewish shop in sight and many houses, and arrested thousands of, of men, put them in concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I understand that they only were-- some of them, not all of them-- some of them were let out on the-- on the promise, A, to give their entire assets, make them over to the-- to the government, to the Reich-- and, B, to leave Germany.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Now, it wasn't easy to leave Germany, I should add.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "At that time, as you know, there was no place to go.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "So--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We went into hiding.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had some advance warning.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "These things were-- somehow, there was a very effective grapevine in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, and Jewish circles got wind of what was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Besides, you didn't have to get wind of it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The way in which the press painted and covered this incident-- the, the, the assassination, the murder of vom Rath by, by Grynszpan-- was enough to make you pretty sure that something-- you didn't know what-- but something was going to come that was not pleasant.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so my father spent-- we left in-- I think the Kristallnacht was the night of November 10.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was either the previous night, or I think it was the morning of that same day that--",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
